In the morning mist, the faint snuffles of deer break the valley's silence. Tiebu Nature Reserve sits at an altitude of more than 3,000 meters in southwest China's Sichuan Province. These mountains and valleys are home to China's largest population of wild sika deer. About 'Journeys in Nature': Aba series: Located on the southeastern edge of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Aba Prefecture is rich in diverse ecosystems, such as forests, grasslands, wetlands and glaciers. Stay tuned and explore this hidden land. More on the Aba series: Aba Series | Episode 1: Dagu glacier Aba Series | Episode 3: Baby cranes Aba Series | Episode 4: Fairy lake Aba Series | Episode 5: Zogye wetland Aba Series | Episode 6: A joyful land Aba Series | Episode 7: Nyanpo Yutse Aba Series | Episode 8: Sichuan sika deer (Cover image a screenshot from the video) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)